i3wm Keybindings cheat sheet (standalone Ubuntu):

 = windows key (Mod4)

# start alacritty terminal
+Return

# kill focused window
+q

# Application menu search (Rofi):
+d

# Window switcher menu (Rofi):
+t

# Power menu (lock/logout/reboot/shutdown):
+Shift+e

# Lock the system (blur-lock)
+l

# reload the configuration file
+Shift+c

# restart i3 inplace
+Shift+r

# keybinding hint in rofi
F1

# change window focus
+j focus left
+k focus down
+b focus up
+o focus right

# alternatively, you can use the cursor keys:
+Left focus left
+Down focus down
+Up focus up
+Right focus right

# move a focused window
+Shift+j move left
+Shift+k move down
+Shift+b move up
+Shift+o move right

# alternatively, you can use the cursor keys:
+Shift+Left move left
+Shift+Down move down
+Shift+Up move up
+Shift+Right move right

# split in horizontal orientation
+h split h

# split in vertical orientation
+v split v

# enter fullscreen mode for the focused container
+f fullscreen toggle

# change container layout (stacked, tabbed, toggle split)
+s layout stacking
+g layout tabbed
+e layout toggle split

# toggle tiling / floating
+Shift+space floating toggle

# change focus between tiling / floating windows
+space focus mode_toggle

# focus the parent container
+a focus parent

# resize mode
+r enters resize mode

# resize floating window
+right mouse button

# switch between workspaces
+Tab next workspace
+Shift+Tab previous workspace

# open new empty workspace
+Shift+n

## Multimedia Keys

# Toggle audio output device
+p

# Power profiles switcher (rofi)
+Shift+p

## App shortcuts
+w starts Vivaldi
+n starts Nautilus
Print screenshot

## Volume/Brightness
XF86AudioRaiseVolume  volume up (with OSD)
XF86AudioLowerVolume  volume down (with OSD)
XF86AudioMute         mute toggle (with OSD)
XF86MonBrightnessUp   brightness up (with OSD)
XF86MonBrightnessDown brightness down (with OSD)
